				\begin{document}$$K_1, K_2$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M24"><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>K</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>K</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2023_5613_Article_IEq12.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> are connected by an oriented edge if and only if the two <italic>k</italic>-mers overlap by <inline-formula id="IEq13"><alternatives><tex-math id="M25">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
